    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-29T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90H/33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-29T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 29, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 29—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>548. Department’s 209, June 6, 5 p.m. Afghans still unwilling to accept
                    phraseology of article 4 in accordance with the Department’s original draft,
                    being embarrassed by the use of the words “most favored nation” treatment.</p>
                <p>In order to get around this difficulty might I be authorized<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d426fn10">Authorization was granted in Department’s telegram No.
                        263, July 3, 6 p.m.</note> to propose the substitution of the text of
                    present article 4 by the article on the most favored nation clause contained on
                    page 12 of the general provisions for inclusion in trade agreements forwarded
                    with Department’s circular instruction diplomatic serial number 2572 of June 6,
                        1935.<note n="11" xml:id="d426fn11">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
